# Repositry of Android application

Android users can install the [[http://fdroid.org]] client and add the official Nit-Droid repository and benefit bleeding-edge state of the art.

In the F-Droid client:

1. Manage repository (in the menu)
2. Add a repository (plus icon)
3. Enter the address [[http://nitlanguage.org/fdroid]]  
4. Update (update icon)

The source code of the applications in the F-Droid repository is available in the [[`examples` directory|http://nitlanguage.org/nit.git/tree/HEAD:/examples]].

These applications are compiled by the Nit tools.
